               <p>JOHN SHEDDEN SCRimgEOUR. On the 25th of August I felt something at my pocket, I turned round and collared a man, but I cannot say it was the prisoner - the officer came and took him - the officer took up my handkerchief, which was safe an hour before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-440-person2282">
                  HENRY 
                  HUGHES
               <interp inst="t18260914-440-person2282" type="surname" value="HUGHES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-440-person2282" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-440-person2282" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the watchman; I saw the prisoner and two others following the prosecutor about fifteen yards; I saw the prisoner put his hand into the pocket, and then the other two went away - I crossed over, and saw the handkerchief on the ground - I seized the prisoner, and took up the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by Mr. PHILLIPS. Q. Were there not a great many people about? A. Yes; there was a dreadful storm at the time - the lightning did not frighten me.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
